Vice President Biden spoke with Sudanese Second Vice President Ali Osman Taha about the upcoming referendum on the status of Southern Sudan. The Vice President emphasized the United States' commitment to an on-time referendum and the importance of Sudanese commitment to finding a negotiated path forward on critical outstanding issues. He expressed concern about engagement with armed proxies and encouraged the Sudanese government to be reassuring and responsible in its messages and policies toward southerners in the north. Both leaders agreed that a positive relationship between Northern and Southern Sudan, regardless of the referendum outcome, is important for all Sudanese people, regional stability, and the U.S.-Sudan relationship.